[thinking] I'm considering how Java serialization works, specifically that it only calls private writeObject/readObject if the class is serializable and properly declares a private void writeObject, which it does. However, I noticed a coverage failure related to `replaceObject` not triggering in native, possibly because writeObject wasn't executed. I think our first test failed because of serialization metadata issues, which led to default field writing without replacements. There might be a problem with direct MethodHandle access as well.
